==English==
===Noun===
'''interview'''
#A [[formal]] [[meeting]], [[in person]], for the [[assessment]] of a [[candidate]] or [[applicant]]
#* It was a dreadful '''interview'''; I have no hope of getting the job
#A [[conversation]] in which [[fact]]s or [[opinion]]s are [[sought]]
#* The reporter gave the witness an '''interview'''
#The [[account]] of such a conversation
#* The '''interview''' was printed the next day

====Translations====
*Finnish: [[haastattelu]] (1,2,3)
*French: [[entrevue]]
*Japanese: [[面接]] ([[めんせつ]], ''mensetsu'')
*Portuguese: [[entrevista]]
*Korean: [[면접]] (''myŏnjŏp'')

===Verb===
'''to interview''' [[transitive]] and [[intransitive]]
#To obtain an interview with someone; and to have an interview
#* He '''interviewed''' the witness
#* The witness was '''interviewed'''

====Translations====
*Finnish: [[haastatella]] (1)
*French: [[avoir]] une [[entrevue]]; interroger (esp. by the police)
*Japanese: [[面接]][[する]] ([[めんせつ]][[する]], ''mensetsu suru'')
*Portuguese: [[fazer]] [[entrevista]]
*Korean: [[면접]][[하다]] (''myŏnjŏp hada'')

